    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-11-24T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-11-24T23:00:00-05:00" n="399"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d399">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.5/11–2551: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The United States Delegation at the Eighth Session of the
                        North Atlantic Council to the Acting Secretary of State</hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d399fn1">Repeated to London, Paris for <gloss
                            target="#t_SHAPE1">SHAPE</gloss>, Brussels, The Hague, Copenhagen, Oslo,
                        Reykjavik, Lisbon, Athens, Ankara, Ottawa, and Luxembourg.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-11-25T05:00:00+01:00"
                            >November 25, 1951—5 a. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Secto1">Secto</gloss> 77. Fol adopted this afternoon<note
                        n="2" xml:id="d399fn2">The agenda was approved at the second meeting of the
                        Council on Saturday, November 24. A record of this meeting is printed <hi
                            rend="italic">infra</hi>.</note> as agenda 8th session:</p>
                <p>I. Opening statements.</p>
                <p>II. Adoption of: <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>Agenda.</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>Press regulations.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>III. Reports by permanent <gloss target="#t_NATO1">NAT</gloss> agencies: <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>Mil Committee.</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>Civilian agencies. <list>
                                <label>(<hi rend="italic">a</hi>)</label>
                                <item>Council Deputies.</item>
                                <label>(<hi rend="italic">b</hi>)</label>
                                <item>
                                    <gloss target="#t_DPB1">DPB</gloss>.</item>
                                <label>(<hi rend="italic">c</hi>)</label>
                                <item>
                                    <gloss target="#t_FEB1">FEB</gloss>.</item>
                            </list>
                        </item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>IV. Exchange of views on polit matters.</p>
                <p>V. Estimate of relative strength and capabilities of <gloss target="#t_NATO1"
                        >NATO</gloss> and Sov bloc forces at present and in immed future.</p>
                <p>VI. Report on readiness and effectiveness of <gloss target="#t_NATO1"
                        >NATO</gloss> forces.</p>
                <p>VII. Statement on progress of work of <gloss target="#t_TCC1">TCC</gloss>.</p>
                <p>VIII. Statement by Gen <persName corresp="#p_E1">Eisenhower</persName>.</p>
                <p>IX. Ger participation in Western defense.</p>
                <p>X. Report by Committee on North Atlantic Community.</p>
                <p>XI. Other business, including date and place of next mtg of Council.</p>
                <p>XII. Communiqué.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_ADG1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
